---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <header class="container container-medium my-5 py-5 text-center pt-5">
    <section>
      <Image src="/gephi-logo.svg" class="mb-3 mb-md-0" alt="Gephi logo" width="240" height="240" />
      <h1>Welcome to Gephi</h1>
      <h2>the Open Graph Viz platform</h2>

      <p class="fs-3 mb-0">
        Gephi is an <strong>open-source</strong> project dedicated to helping people <strong
          >visually analyze networks</strong
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
  </header>

  <main class="my-5 py-5">
    <section class="container">
      <!-- Main applications -->
      <div class="row mb-5">
        <div class="col-6">
          <p class="text-center">
            <a href="/gephi"
              ><Image
                src="/gephi-screenshot.jpg"
                alt="Gephi screenshot"
                width="600"
                height="300"
                class="shadow border mw-100 h-auto"
              /></a
            >
          </p>
          <h3>Gephi</h3>
          <p>
            Our flagship Java-based desktop software offers robust features for comprehensive network analysis and
            visualization. Ideal for in-depth work, it supports large-scale network data and complex layouts.
          </p>
          <p class="text-center">
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/gephi">Download</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-6">
          <p class="text-center">
            <a href="/gephi-lite">
              <Image
                src="/gephi-lite-screenshot.png"
                alt="Gephi Lite screenshot"
                width="600"
                height="300"
                class="shadow border mw-100 h-auto"
              /></a
            >
          </p>
          <h3>Gephi Lite</h3>
          <p>
            A streamlined web version of Gephi, Gephi Lite allows for quick and easy network visualization and analysis
            directly in your browser. Perfect for getting started or for lightweight projects.
          </p>
          <p class="text-center">
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/gephi-lite">Try online</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Secondary applications -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-4">
          <p class="text-center">
            <a href="https://jacomyma.github.io/gephisto/">
              <Image
                src="/gephisto-hipster.png"
                alt="Gephisto Hipster"
                width="200"
                height="300"
                class="shadow border mw-100 h-auto"
              /></a
            >
          </p>
          <h3>Gephisto</h3>
          <p>A web application to generate network maps in <strong>one click</strong>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-4">
          <p class="text-center">
            <a href="https://github.com/gephi/gephi-toolkit">
              <Image
                src="/gephi-toolkit-illustration.png"
                alt="A toolkit"
                width="600"
                height="300"
                class="shadow border mw-100 h-auto"
              /></a
            >
          </p>
          <h3>Gephi Toolkit</h3>
          <p>
            The Gephi Toolkit packages key modules (Graph, Layout, Filters, IOâ€¦) into a Java library for any project.
            This JAR file enables Java applications to perform Gephi tasks automatically, like command-line programs,
            enhancing their capabilities and utility.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-4">
          <p class="text-center">
            <a href="https://gephi.org/plugins/#/">
              <Image
                src="/gephi-plugins-illustration.jpg"
                alt="A nice customized car, as a metaphor for customizing Gephi with plugins"
                width="600"
                height="300"
                class="shadow border mw-100 h-auto"
              /></a
            >
          </p>
          <h3>Gephi Plugins</h3>
          <p>
            A collection of plugins to enhance your version of Gephi. They are related to layers, metrics, data import,
            etc...
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <br />

    <section class="my-5 py-5">
      <div class="container container-large">
        <h2 class="text-center">...but Gephi is also its <strong>community</strong></h2>
        <p>
          The Gephi community is crucial to its success. Open source contributions from global developers drive
          continuous improvement. Community-made resources like tutorials and plugins enhance accessibility. Scientific
          papers validate its effectiveness, and conferences foster collaboration and knowledge exchange. This
          collective effort makes Gephi a powerful tool for network analysis and visualization.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row mb-5">
          <div class="col-4">
            <p class="text-center">
              <Image src="/sponsor-illustration.svg" alt="" width="200" height="200" class="mw-100 h-auto" />
            </p>
            <h3>Sponsor Gephi</h3>
            <p>
              You can financially support Gephi through <a href="https://opencollective.com/gephi">Open Collective</a>.
              Money pays developers and community events.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="col-4">
            <p class="text-center">
              <Image src="/help-illustration.svg" alt="" width="200" height="200" class="mw-100 h-auto" />
            </p>
            <h3>Share your expertise</h3>
            <p>
              There are many Gephi users who could use some help! You can help by them on <a
                href="https://github.com/gephi/gephi/discussions">GitHub discussions</a
              >, <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/gephi">StackOverflow</a> or <a
                href="https://www.reddit.com/r/gephi">Reddit</a
              >.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="col-4">
            <p class="text-center">
              <Image src="/code-illustration.svg" alt="" width="200" height="200" class="mw-100 h-auto" />
            </p>
            <h3>Contribute</h3>
            <p>
              Gephi is and will remain <strong>open source</strong>. Whether you are a Java developer or a web
              developer, you could help <a href="https://github.com/gephi/gephi/issues">fixing issues</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
